    <text id="A8055T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Frankhouser tries to collect debt from McCue.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Piper &amp; Frankhouser<lb/><hi rend="underline">1860</hi>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1860-06-20">June '20th 60</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Mr. J H McCue<lb/>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>We wrote to you a few days at Nelson C House, but suppose you did not receive it.</p>
                <p>Our object now is to say to you that your first note for 86 50/100 $ was due on
                    the 15th inst. what can we depend upon.</p>
                <p>We would be glad if you could make arrangements to pay it now, as we really need
                    help now.</p>


                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully your<lb/>friend</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">Piper Frankhouser</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
